12/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkey will host a joint military exercise in the Mediterranean Sea next week with Israel and the United States, the Israeli army announced on Tuesday (August 11th).
Eight ships, four helicopters and three search-and-rescue planes from the three armies will participate in the exercise dubbed "Reliant Mermaid".
Its goal is to boost co-ordination and co-operation among Turkish, Israeli and US forces in emergency situations.
(Hurriyet, Anadolu news agency, AFP, Trend - 11/08/09)
